    "2 LLMs are trained using an iterative process known as reinforcement learning with human feedback (Fig. 1).",
    "In this approach, the model produces various outputs and humans rank them according to their preferences, guiding the model toward a desired state.",
    "The technique has delivered highly fluent text, but in health care, more emphasis must be placed on factual correctness.",
    "This could be accomplished by placing greater reward weights on accuracy, involving more domain experts in the refinement process, and constructing datasets with enhanced salience of ground truths.",
    "Moreover, to mitigate the potential for bias, training data should be representative of the patient population on which a model will be used."
  ],
